evaluation.response:
It sucks to feel left out and invisible, especially when you used to be so connected with your team.&#x20;

Recovering from an injury can be tough enough physically, but the emotional and mental side of it can be just as challenging. Feeling left out or invisible is really common, especially if you're used to being a big part of the team.&#x20;

Just know you're still a part of the team, even if you're not active on the field right now. Those drills and memes might seem like a distant memory for you, but they're just a reminder of the camaraderie and fun times you've had with your teammates.&#x20;

I know it's hard to see right now, but this is part of the process to become stronger and improve and come up even stronger next year.&#x20;
